{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Today I'd like to show you"},{"time":2000,"text":"the future of the way we make things."},{"time":4000,"text":"I believe that soon our buildings and machines"},{"time":6000,"text":"will be self-assembling,"},{"time":8000,"text":"replicating and repairing themselves."},{"time":10000,"text":"So I'm going to show you"},{"time":12000,"text":"what I believe is the current state of manufacturing,"},{"time":14000,"text":"and then compare that to some natural systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17000,"text":"So in the current state of manufacturing, we have skyscrapers --"},{"time":20000,"text":"two and a half years [of assembly time],"},{"time":22000,"text":"500,000 to a million parts,"},{"time":24000,"text":"fairly complex,"},{"time":26000,"text":"new, exciting technologies in steel, concrete, glass."},{"time":29000,"text":"We have exciting machines"},{"time":31000,"text":"that can take us into space --"},{"time":33000,"text":"five years [of assembly time], 2.5 million parts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36000,"text":"But on the other side, if you look at the natural systems,"},{"time":39000,"text":"we have proteins"},{"time":41000,"text":"that have two million types,"},{"time":43000,"text":"can fold in 10,000 nanoseconds,"},{"time":45000,"text":"or DNA with three billion base pairs"},{"time":47000,"text":"we can replicate in roughly an hour."},{"time":50000,"text":"So there's all of this complexity"},{"time":52000,"text":"in our natural systems,"},{"time":54000,"text":"but they're extremely efficient,"},{"time":56000,"text":"far more efficient than anything we can build,"},{"time":58000,"text":"far more complex than anything we can build."},{"time":60000,"text":"They're far more efficient in terms of energy."},{"time":62000,"text":"They hardly ever make mistakes."},{"time":65000,"text":"And they can repair themselves for longevity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"So there's something super interesting about natural systems."},{"time":70000,"text":"And if we can translate that"},{"time":72000,"text":"into our built environment,"},{"time":74000,"text":"then there's some exciting potential for the way that we build things."},{"time":76000,"text":"And I think the key to that is self-assembly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"So if we want to utilize self-assembly in our physical environment,"},{"time":82000,"text":"I think there's four key factors."},{"time":84000,"text":"The first is that we need to decode"},{"time":86000,"text":"all of the complexity of what we want to build --"},{"time":88000,"text":"so our buildings and machines."},{"time":90000,"text":"And we need to decode that into simple sequences --"},{"time":92000,"text":"basically the DNA of how our buildings work."},{"time":94000,"text":"Then we need programmable parts"},{"time":96000,"text":"that can take that sequence"},{"time":98000,"text":"and use that to fold up, or reconfigure."},{"time":101000,"text":"We need some energy that's going to allow that to activate,"},{"time":104000,"text":"allow our parts to be able to fold up from the program."},{"time":107000,"text":"And we need some type of error correction redundancy"},{"time":109000,"text":"to guarantee that we have successfully built what we want."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"So I'm going to show you a number of projects"},{"time":114000,"text":"that my colleagues and I at MIT are working on"},{"time":116000,"text":"to achieve this self-assembling future."},{"time":118000,"text":"The first two are the MacroBot and DeciBot."},{"time":121000,"text":"So these projects are large-scale reconfigurable robots --"},{"time":125000,"text":"8 ft., 12 ft. long proteins."},{"time":128000,"text":"They're embedded with mechanical electrical devices, sensors."},{"time":131000,"text":"You decode what you want to fold up into,"},{"time":133000,"text":"into a sequence of angles --"},{"time":135000,"text":"so negative 120, negative 120, 0, 0,"},{"time":137000,"text":"120, negative 120 -- something like that;"},{"time":140000,"text":"so a sequence of angles, or turns,"},{"time":142000,"text":"and you send that sequence through the string."},{"time":145000,"text":"Each unit takes its message -- so negative 120 --"},{"time":148000,"text":"it rotates to that, checks if it got there"},{"time":150000,"text":"and then passes it to its neighbor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"So these are the brilliant scientists,"},{"time":155000,"text":"engineers, designers that worked on this project."},{"time":157000,"text":"And I think it really brings to light:"},{"time":159000,"text":"Is this really scalable?"},{"time":161000,"text":"I mean, thousands of dollars, lots of man hours"},{"time":163000,"text":"made to make this eight-foot robot."},{"time":166000,"text":"Can we really scale this up? Can we really embed robotics into every part?"},{"time":169000,"text":"The next one questions that"},{"time":171000,"text":"and looks at passive nature,"},{"time":173000,"text":"or passively trying to have reconfiguration programmability."},{"time":176000,"text":"But it goes a step further,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and it tries to have actual computation."},{"time":180000,"text":"It basically embeds the most fundamental building block of computing,"},{"time":182000,"text":"the digital logic gate,"},{"time":184000,"text":"directly into your parts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"So this is a NAND gate."},{"time":188000,"text":"You have one tetrahedron which is the gate"},{"time":190000,"text":"that's going to do your computing,"},{"time":192000,"text":"and you have two input tetrahedrons."},{"time":194000,"text":"One of them is the input from the user, as you're building your bricks."},{"time":197000,"text":"The other one is from the previous brick that was placed."},{"time":200000,"text":"And then it gives you an output in 3D space."},{"time":203000,"text":"So what this means"},{"time":205000,"text":"is that the user can start plugging in what they want the bricks to do."},{"time":208000,"text":"It computes on what it was doing before"},{"time":210000,"text":"and what you said you wanted it to do."},{"time":212000,"text":"And now it starts moving in three-dimensional space --"},{"time":214000,"text":"so up or down."},{"time":216000,"text":"So on the left-hand side, [1,1] input equals 0 output, which goes down."},{"time":219000,"text":"On the right-hand side,"},{"time":221000,"text":"[0,0] input is a 1 output, which goes up."},{"time":224000,"text":"And so what that really means"},{"time":226000,"text":"is that our structures now contain the blueprints"},{"time":228000,"text":"of what we want to build."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230000,"text":"So they have all of the information embedded in them of what was constructed."},{"time":233000,"text":"So that means that we can have some form of self-replication."},{"time":236000,"text":"In this case I call it self-guided replication,"},{"time":239000,"text":"because your structure contains the exact blueprints."},{"time":241000,"text":"If you have errors, you can replace a part."},{"time":243000,"text":"All the local information is embedded to tell you how to fix it."},{"time":246000,"text":"So you could have something that climbs along and reads it"},{"time":248000,"text":"and can output at one to one."},{"time":250000,"text":"It's directly embedded; there's no external instructions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"So the last project I'll show is called Biased Chains,"},{"time":255000,"text":"and it's probably the most exciting example that we have right now"},{"time":258000,"text":"of passive self-assembly systems."},{"time":260000,"text":"So it takes the reconfigurability"},{"time":262000,"text":"and programmability"},{"time":264000,"text":"and makes it a completely passive system."},{"time":268000,"text":"So basically you have a chain of elements."},{"time":270000,"text":"Each element is completely identical,"},{"time":272000,"text":"and they're biased."},{"time":274000,"text":"So each chain, or each element, wants to turn right or left."},{"time":277000,"text":"So as you assemble the chain, you're basically programming it."},{"time":280000,"text":"You're telling each unit if it should turn right or left."},{"time":283000,"text":"So when you shake the chain,"},{"time":286000,"text":"it then folds up"},{"time":288000,"text":"into any configuration that you've programmed in --"},{"time":291000,"text":"so in this case, a spiral,"},{"time":293000,"text":"or in this case,"},{"time":296000,"text":"two cubes next to each other."},{"time":299000,"text":"So you can basically program"},{"time":301000,"text":"any three-dimensional shape --"},{"time":303000,"text":"or one-dimensional, two-dimensional -- up into this chain completely passively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"So what does this tell us about the future?"},{"time":308000,"text":"I think that it's telling us"},{"time":310000,"text":"that there's new possibilities for self-assembly, replication, repair"},{"time":313000,"text":"in our physical structures, our buildings, machines."},{"time":316000,"text":"There's new programmability in these parts."},{"time":318000,"text":"And from that you have new possibilities for computing."},{"time":320000,"text":"We'll have spatial computing."},{"time":322000,"text":"Imagine if our buildings, our bridges, machines,"},{"time":324000,"text":"all of our bricks could actually compute."},{"time":326000,"text":"That's amazing parallel and distributed computing power,"},{"time":328000,"text":"new design possibilities."},{"time":330000,"text":"So it's exciting potential for this."},{"time":332000,"text":"So I think these projects I've showed here"},{"time":334000,"text":"are just a tiny step towards this future,"},{"time":336000,"text":"if we implement these new technologies"},{"time":338000,"text":"for a new self-assembling world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}